pgmMIB.description: The MIB module for managing PGM implementations.

pgmNeEnable.name: pgmNeEnable
pgmNeEnable.description: Enable/Disable Parameter indicates whether this PGM operation is enabled or disabled.

pgmNeSessionLifeTime.name: pgmNeSessionLifeTime
pgmNeSessionLifeTime.description: The length of the idle time (seconds) following which a PGM session will be aged out. An idle PGM session means there is no SPM message received from the upstream. Value of 0 indicates no timeout.

pgmNeMaxReXmitStates.name: pgmNeMaxReXmitStates
pgmNeMaxReXmitStates.description: The Maximum number of retransmission state entries. The value of -1 means network element has no limitation. The value of -2 means not supported by this implementation.

pgmNeMaxSessions.name: pgmNeMaxSessions
pgmNeMaxSessions.description: The maximum number of state sessions supported. The value of -1 means network element has no limitation. The value of -2 means not supported by this implementation.

pgmNeTotalInterfacesNumberOfEntries.name: pgmNeTotalInterfacesNumberOfEntries
pgmNeTotalInterfacesNumberOfEntries.description: The total number of entries in the PGM Interface table.

pgmNeIfConfigTable.name: pgmNeIfConfigTable
pgmNeIfConfigTable.description: The table holding per interface configuration information relating to PGM Network Element operation.

pgmNeIfConfigIndex.name: pgmNeIfConfigIndex
pgmNeIfConfigIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

pgmNeIfPgmEnable.name: pgmNeIfPgmEnable
pgmNeIfPgmEnable.description: Allows PGM to be enabled and disabled per Network Interface. PGM can be enabled or disabled per Network Interface, only if PGM is enabled for this Network Element.

pgmNeIfNakRptInterval.name: pgmNeIfNakRptInterval
pgmNeIfNakRptInterval.description: The length of time (milliseconds) for which a network element will repeat a NAK while waiting for a corresponding NCF. This interval is counted down from the transmission of a NAK.

pgmNeIfNakRptRate.name: pgmNeIfNakRptRate
pgmNeIfNakRptRate.description: The rate at which NAKs are repeated.

pgmNeIfNakRdataInterval.name: pgmNeIfNakRdataInterval
pgmNeIfNakRdataInterval.description: The length of time (milliseconds) for which a network element will wait for the corresponding RDATA. This interval is counted down from the time a matching NCF is received. This value must be greater than the pgmNeIfNakEliminateInterval.

pgmNeIfNakEliminateInterval.name: pgmNeIfNakEliminateInterval
pgmNeIfNakEliminateInterval.description: The length of time (milliseconds) for which a network element will eliminate NAKs for a specific TSI/SQN. This interval is counted down from the time the first NAK is established. This value must be smaller than pgmNeIfNakRdataInterval.

pgmNeIfPerformanceTable.name: pgmNeIfPerformanceTable
pgmNeIfPerformanceTable.description: The table holding per interface performance information related to PGM Network Element operation.

pgmNeIfPerformanceEntry.name: pgmNeIfPerformanceEntry
pgmNeIfPerformanceEntry.description: Per Interface Information for Network Elements.

pgmNeIfPerformanceIndex.name: pgmNeIfPerformanceIndex
pgmNeIfPerformanceIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

pgmNeIfReXmitStates.name: pgmNeIfReXmitStates
pgmNeIfReXmitStates.description: The total retransmit state entries for this interface.

pgmNeIfReXmitTimedOut.name: pgmNeIfReXmitTimedOut
pgmNeIfReXmitTimedOut.description: The total number of timed-out retransmit state entries for this interface.

pgmNeIfInSpms.name: pgmNeIfInSpms
pgmNeIfInSpms.description: The total number of SPMs received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutSpms.name: pgmNeIfOutSpms
pgmNeIfOutSpms.description: The total number of SPMs sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfInParitySpms.name: pgmNeIfInParitySpms
pgmNeIfInParitySpms.description: The total number of parity SPMs received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutParitySpms.name: pgmNeIfOutParitySpms
pgmNeIfOutParitySpms.description: The total number of parity SPMs sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfInRdata.name: pgmNeIfInRdata
pgmNeIfInRdata.description: The total number of RDATA received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutRdata.name: pgmNeIfOutRdata
pgmNeIfOutRdata.description: The total number of RDATA sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfInParityRdata.name: pgmNeIfInParityRdata
pgmNeIfInParityRdata.description: The total number of parity RDATA received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutParityRdata.name: pgmNeIfOutParityRdata
pgmNeIfOutParityRdata.description: The total number of parity RDATA sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfInRdataNoSessionErrors.name: pgmNeIfInRdataNoSessionErrors
pgmNeIfInRdataNoSessionErrors.description: The number of received RDATA discarded because of no session.

pgmNeIfUniqueNaks.name: pgmNeIfUniqueNaks
pgmNeIfUniqueNaks.description: The total number of unique NAKs received on this interface.

pgmNeIfInNaks.name: pgmNeIfInNaks
pgmNeIfInNaks.description: The total number of NAKs received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutNaks.name: pgmNeIfOutNaks
pgmNeIfOutNaks.description: The total number of NAKs sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfUniqueParityNaks.name: pgmNeIfUniqueParityNaks
pgmNeIfUniqueParityNaks.description: The total number of unique parity NAKs received on this interface.

pgmNeIfInParityNaks.name: pgmNeIfInParityNaks
pgmNeIfInParityNaks.description: The total number of parity NAKs received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutParityNaks.name: pgmNeIfOutParityNaks
pgmNeIfOutParityNaks.description: The total number of parity NAKs sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfInNakNoSessionErrors.name: pgmNeIfInNakNoSessionErrors
pgmNeIfInNakNoSessionErrors.description: The number of received NAKs discarded because of no session.

pgmNeIfInNakSeqErrors.name: pgmNeIfInNakSeqErrors
pgmNeIfInNakSeqErrors.description: The number of received NAKs discarded because of out of sequence (out of retransmit window).

pgmNeIfInParityNakTgErrors.name: pgmNeIfInParityNakTgErrors
pgmNeIfInParityNakTgErrors.description: The number of received parity NAKs discarded because out of parity TG window.

pgmNeIfInNnaks.name: pgmNeIfInNnaks
pgmNeIfInNnaks.description: The total number of NNAKs received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutNnaks.name: pgmNeIfOutNnaks
pgmNeIfOutNnaks.description: The total number of NNAKs sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfInParityNnaks.description: The total number of parity NNAKs received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutParityNnaks.name: pgmNeIfOutParityNnaks
pgmNeIfOutParityNnaks.description: The total number of parity NNAKs sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfInNnakNoSessionErrors.name: pgmNeIfInNnakNoSessionErrors
pgmNeIfInNnakNoSessionErrors.description: The number of received NNAKs discarded because of no session.

pgmNeIfInNcfs.name: pgmNeIfInNcfs
pgmNeIfInNcfs.description: The total number of NCFs received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutNcfs.name: pgmNeIfOutNcfs
pgmNeIfOutNcfs.description: The total number of NCFs sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfInParityNcfs.name: pgmNeIfInParityNcfs
pgmNeIfInParityNcfs.description: The total number of parity NCFs received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfOutParityNcfs.name: pgmNeIfOutParityNcfs
pgmNeIfOutParityNcfs.description: The total number of parity NCFs sent out from the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfInNcfNoSessionErrors.name: pgmNeIfInNcfNoSessionErrors
pgmNeIfInNcfNoSessionErrors.description: The number of received NCFs discarded because of no session.

pgmNeIfInRedirectNcfs.name: pgmNeIfInRedirectNcfs
pgmNeIfInRedirectNcfs.description: The number of redirected NCFs received on the PGM interface.

pgmNeIfSpmFromSource.name: pgmNeIfSpmFromSource
pgmNeIfSpmFromSource.description: Number of SPM packets received from source.

pgmNeIfSpmBadSqn.name: pgmNeIfSpmBadSqn
pgmNeIfSpmBadSqn.description: Number of SPM packets discarded due to bad SQN.

pgmNeIfSpmError.name: pgmNeIfSpmError
pgmNeIfSpmError.description: Number of SPM packets discarded due to operational error. Some examples of operational errors are failure to create TSI state for SPM, parity SPM for a TSI with no parity.

pgmNeIfPollRandomIgnore.name: pgmNeIfPollRandomIgnore
pgmNeIfPollRandomIgnore.description: Number of POLL packets not replied due to random condition failing.

pgmNeIfPollTsiStateError.name: pgmNeIfPollTsiStateError
pgmNeIfPollTsiStateError.description: Number of POLL packets discarded due to no matching TSI state.

pgmNeIfPollParentError.name: pgmNeIfPollParentError
pgmNeIfPollParentError.description: Number of POLL packets discarded due to unknown parent.

pgmNeIfPollTypeError.name: pgmNeIfPollTypeError
pgmNeIfPollTypeError.description: Number of POLL packets discarded due to failed type matching.

pgmNeIfPollError.name: pgmNeIfPollError
pgmNeIfPollError.description: Number of POLL packets discarded due to operational error.

pgmNeIfPollOriginated.name: pgmNeIfPollOriginated
pgmNeIfPollOriginated.description: Number of polls originated on this interface.

pgmNeIfPolrNoState.name: pgmNeIfPolrNoState
pgmNeIfPolrNoState.description: Number of POLRs discarded due to no matching state.

pgmNeIfPolrError.name: pgmNeIfPolrError
pgmNeIfPolrError.description: Number of POLRs discarded due to operational error.

pgmNeIfPolrParityError.name: pgmNeIfPolrParityError
pgmNeIfPolrParityError.description: Number of parity POLRs received for non-parity TSI.

pgmNeIfPolrOriginated.name: pgmNeIfPolrOriginated
pgmNeIfPolrOriginated.description: Number of POLRs originated by this interface.

pgmNeIfNcfError.name: pgmNeIfNcfError
pgmNeIfNcfError.description: Number of NCFs ignored due to no packet memory, due to packet processing errors.

pgmNeIfNcfParityError.name: pgmNeIfNcfParityError
pgmNeIfNcfParityError.description: Number of NCFs ignored. Incremented when a parity NCF is received on a session for which no parity capability has been advertised in the session's SPMs.

pgmNeIfNcfPartialParity.name: pgmNeIfNcfPartialParity
pgmNeIfNcfPartialParity.description: Number of NCFs ignored due to not enough parity blocks acknowledged.

pgmNeIfNcfReceived.name: pgmNeIfNcfReceived
pgmNeIfNcfReceived.description: Number of NCFs that confirm an outstanding NAK.

pgmNeIfNcfAnticipated.name: pgmNeIfNcfAnticipated
pgmNeIfNcfAnticipated.description: Number of NCFs that cause NAK anticipation.

pgmNeIfNcfRedirecting.name: pgmNeIfNcfRedirecting
pgmNeIfNcfRedirecting.description: Number of NCFs received as consequence of redirected NAK.

pgmNeIfNakEliminated.name: pgmNeIfNakEliminated
pgmNeIfNakEliminated.description: Number of NAKs eliminated by retransmission state.

pgmNeIfNakError.name: pgmNeIfNakError
pgmNeIfNakError.description: Number of errors creating retransmission state or NAK, due to NAK packet processing.

pgmNeIfNakParityError.name: pgmNeIfNakParityError
pgmNeIfNakParityError.description: Number of NAKs ignored, due to no parity available. Incremented when parity NAK is received on this session, for which no parity capability has been advartised.

pgmNeIfNNakEliminated.name: pgmNeIfNNakEliminated
pgmNeIfNNakEliminated.description: Number of NNAKs eliminated by retransmission state.

pgmNeIfNNakError.name: pgmNeIfNNakError
pgmNeIfNNakError.description: Number of errors encountered creating retransmission state OR nak.

pgmNeIfNNakParityError.name: pgmNeIfNNakParityError
pgmNeIfNNakParityError.description: Number of Null NAKs ignored, due to no parity available. Incremented when parity NNAK is received on this session, for which no parity capability has been advartised.

pgmNeIfNNakCongestionReports.name: pgmNeIfNNakCongestionReports
pgmNeIfNNakCongestionReports.description: Number of NAKs forwarded as NNAK as congestion report only.

pgmNeIfNakRetryExpired.name: pgmNeIfNakRetryExpired
pgmNeIfNakRetryExpired.description: The total number of NAKs timed out after retrying.

pgmNeIfNakRetryExpiredDLR.name: pgmNeIfNakRetryExpiredDLR
pgmNeIfNakRetryExpiredDLR.description: Number of NAKs unconfirmed by DLR.

pgmNeIfNakForwardedDLR.name: pgmNeIfNakForwardedDLR
pgmNeIfNakForwardedDLR.description: Number of NAKs forwarded out this i/f to DLR with retransmission state.

pgmNeIfNakRetransmitted.name: pgmNeIfNakRetransmitted
pgmNeIfNakRetransmitted.description: Total number of NAKs retransmitted out this i/f.

pgmNeIfRdataEliminatedOIF.name: pgmNeIfRdataEliminatedOIF
pgmNeIfRdataEliminatedOIF.description: Number of RDATA packets eliminated by lack of OIF's.

pgmNeIfRdataEliminatedSqn.name: pgmNeIfRdataEliminatedSqn
pgmNeIfRdataEliminatedSqn.description: Number of RDATA packets eliminated by lack of SQN.

pgmNeIfInRdataFragments.name: pgmNeIfInRdataFragments
pgmNeIfInRdataFragments.description: Total number of RDATA fragments received.

pgmNeIfRdataFragmentsNoSessionErrors.name: pgmNeIfRdataFragmentsNoSessionErrors
pgmNeIfRdataFragmentsNoSessionErrors.description: Number of RDATA fragments eliminated by lack of GSI.

pgmNeIfRdataFragmentsEliminatedOIF.name: pgmNeIfRdataFragmentsEliminatedOIF
pgmNeIfRdataFragmentsEliminatedOIF.description: Number of RDATA fragments eliminated by lack of OIFs.

pgmNeIfRdataFragmentsEliminatedSqn.name: pgmNeIfRdataFragmentsEliminatedSqn
pgmNeIfRdataFragmentsEliminatedSqn.description: Number of RDATA fragments eliminated by lack of SQN.

pgmNeIfOutRdataFragments.name: pgmNeIfOutRdataFragments
pgmNeIfOutRdataFragments.description: Total number of RDATA fragments forwarded.

pgmNeTotalTsiNumberOfEntries.name: pgmNeTotalTsiNumberOfEntries
pgmNeTotalTsiNumberOfEntries.description: The total number of sessions in the PGM NE TSI table.

pgmNeTsiTable.name: pgmNeTsiTable
pgmNeTsiTable.description: The table holding per-tsi state information.

pgmNeTsiEntry.name: pgmNeTsiEntry
pgmNeTsiEntry.description: Transport Session is identified by Global ID and Source Port.

pgmNeTsiGlobalId.name: pgmNeTsiGlobalId
pgmNeTsiGlobalId.description: The Globally unique source identifier for this transport session.

pgmNeTsiUpstreamIfIndex.name: pgmNeTsiUpstreamIfIndex

pgmNeTsiPerformanceGlobalId.description: The Globally unique source identifier for this transport session.

pgmNeTsiTimeout.description: Time left for this entry to expire.

pgmNeTsiLastTtl.name: pgmNeTsiLastTtl

pgmNeTsiPathLossRate.description: Worst reported path loss rate for congestion control. This is reported as a percentage.

pgmNeTsiReceiverLossRate.name: pgmNeTsiReceiverLossRate
pgmNeTsiReceiverLossRate.description: Worst reported receiver loss rate for congestion control. This is reported as a percentage.

pgmNeTsiCongestionReportLead.name: pgmNeTsiCongestionReportLead
pgmNeTsiCongestionReportLead.description: Data lead sequence number associated with the worst reported receiver loss rate.

pgmNeTsiCongestionReportWorstReceiver.name: pgmNeTsiCongestionReportWorstReceiver
pgmNeTsiCongestionReportWorstReceiver.description: IP address of the receiver that reported the worst receiver loss rate.

pgmNeTsiRtxNumberOfEntries.name: pgmNeTsiRtxNumberOfEntries
pgmNeTsiRtxNumberOfEntries.description: Number of entries in the retransmission table.

pgmNeTsiRtxTable.name: pgmNeTsiRtxTable
pgmNeTsiRtxTable.description: The table holding information for every sequence number, or in the case of FEC, every transmission group, for which retransmission has been requested.

pgmNeTsiRtxEntry.name: pgmNeTsiRtxEntry
pgmNeTsiRtxEntry.description: Per sequence number / transmission group information.

pgmNeTsiRtxSequenceNumber.name: pgmNeTsiRtxSequenceNumber
pgmNeTsiRtxSequenceNumber.description: For non-parity retransmission, a sequence number. For parity retransmission, a transmission group and packet count.

pgmNeTsiRtxSequenceNumberType.name: pgmNeTsiRtxSequenceNumberType
pgmNeTsiRtxSequenceNumberType.description: Selective Sequence Number and TG Sequence Number.

pgmNeTsiRtxReqParityTgCount.name: pgmNeTsiRtxReqParityTgCount
pgmNeTsiRtxReqParityTgCount.description: The Requested number of missing parity packets of specific Tg. The largest counter of the received NAK will be stored in this mib. This variable is valid for parity packets only.

pgmNeTsiRtxIfNumberOfEntries.name: pgmNeTsiRtxIfNumberOfEntries
pgmNeTsiRtxIfNumberOfEntries.description: Number of entries in the retransmission interfaces table.

pgmNeTsiRtxIfTable.name: pgmNeTsiRtxIfTable
pgmNeTsiRtxIfTable.description: The table holding information of every interface for which retransmit state for a particular sequence number or transmission group has to be sent.

pgmNeTsiRtxIfEntry.name: pgmNeTsiRtxIfEntry
pgmNeTsiRtxIfEntry.description: Destination interfaces for a particular retransmit state.

pgmNeTsiRtxIfIndex.name: pgmNeTsiRtxIfIndex
pgmNeTsiRtxIfIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

pgmNeTsiRtxIfPacketCount.name: pgmNeTsiRtxIfPacketCount
pgmNeTsiRtxIfPacketCount.description: Number of repair data packets still to be retransmitted on this interface. For non-parity retransmission this will never have a value greater than 1. For parity retransmission, any number can be present.

pgmNeTsiPolrNumberOfEntries.name: pgmNeTsiPolrNumberOfEntries
pgmNeTsiPolrNumberOfEntries.description: Number of entries in the poll response table.

pgmNeTsiPolrTable.name: pgmNeTsiPolrTable
pgmNeTsiPolrTable.description: The table holding state information about what PGM parents are polling this Network Element.

pgmNeTsiPolrEntry.name: pgmNeTsiPolrEntry
pgmNeTsiPolrEntry.description: State information for a Network Element that is being polled by its parents

pgmNeTsiPolrSource.name: pgmNeTsiPolrSource
pgmNeTsiPolrSource.description: IP Address of parent who is polling this device.

pgmNeTsiPolrSequenceNumber.name: pgmNeTsiPolrSequenceNumber
pgmNeTsiPolrSequenceNumber.description: Sequence number of last POLR from the source.

pgmNeTsiPollNumberOfEntries.name: pgmNeTsiPollNumberOfEntries
